You work the problem from the innermost complete ( ), until you get out of the parenthesis, then you simply move to the next set of parenthesis.  It does not matter how awkward the thing as a whole looks, as long as you can remember 
Parenthesis 
Exponent 
Multiplication 
Division 
Addition 
Subtraction 
you can simply clean it up in a much nicer manner.  It's also why those irritating math equations that go viral piss off so many of us.  The are intentionally written in a way to give people issues, they are put out of order, they are simply using symbols with no external grouping... bleh...
